 <text id="A2572T">
  <front id="d2">
   <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
    <p>Hotchkiss writes a brief note to his wife, mentioning his plan to ask for a furlough.</p>
   </div1>
  </front>

  <body id="d4">
   <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
    <head>
     <name type="recipient">Sara A. Hotchkiss</name>
    </head>

    <opener>
     <dateline>
      <date value="1862-12-31">Sat. Morn. Dec. 31<hi rend="super">st</hi> 1862</date>
     </dateline>
     <salute>My Darling --</salute>
    </opener>

    <p>Your letter of the 28<hi rend="super">th</hi> came duly to hand -- and gave me much pleasure
     -- Humphries is going home today and I can only write you a line or so for he just got his
     leave &amp; is off I have gotten over my cold &amp; am very well -- Boswell got back
     yesterday feeling badly for a tragedy that happened while he was gone -- I will tell you about
     it when I have time We had a bad storm -- but it has passed away &amp; is now pleasant -- I
     expect to ask for a furlough in a few days -- My love for you all Be joyous &amp; all keep
     well -- No news the Yanks are stuck in the mud </p>

    <closer>
     <salute>Your loving husband</salute>
     <signed>Jed. Hotchkiss</signed>
    </closer>
   </div1>
  </body>
 </text>
